ReStock

A simple cross-platform .NET MAUI app that uses SQLite for local data storage. Works on Android, iOS, and MacCatalyst.

What You Need

Before running this project, make sure you have:
macOS (latest version recommended)
.NET 10 SDK
Visual Studio for Mac or command-line tools
Java JDK 17 (required for Android builds)
Android SDK with the required API levels installed

Getting Started

Install .NET 10
First, make sure you have .NET 10 installed:
dotnet --version
You should see something like 10.0.xxx.
Install MAUI Workloads
Install the required MAUI tools and workloads:
sudo dotnet workload restore

This ensures you have all the bits needed to build Android, iOS, and MacCatalyst apps.
Install Java JDK 17
Android builds require JDK 17, so let’s make sure you’re using it:
/usr/libexec/java_home -V   # see which JDKs you have
export JAVA_HOME=$(/usr/libexec/java_home -v 17)
export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH
java -version
javac -version


Expected output should show version 17:

openjdk version "17.0.x"
javac 17.0.x

Install Android SDK & API Levels

Check what Android SDK platforms you have:

ls ~/Library/Developer/Xamarin/android-sdk-macosx/platforms/


If you’re missing API 36 (required for this project), install it:

~/Library/Developer/Xamarin/android-sdk-macosx/tools/bin/sdkmanager "platforms;android-36"


Then accept licenses:

dotnet build -t:InstallAndroidDependencies -f net10.0-android -p:AndroidSdkDirectory=~/Library/Developer/Xamarin/android-sdk-macosx -p:AcceptAndroidSDKLicenses=true


Replace ~ with your home directory if needed.

Build and Run
Clean the project
dotnet clean

Build for Android
dotnet build -f net10.0-android

Build for iOS Simulator
dotnet build -f net10.0-ios

Build for MacCatalyst
dotnet build -f net10.0-maccatalyst

Troubleshooting
Java SDK issues

If you see errors about Java or JDK versions:

Exception: Not a directory (Parameter 'homePath')


Make sure JAVA_HOME is pointing to JDK 17:

export JAVA_HOME=$(/usr/libexec/java_home -v 17)
export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH

Missing Android API

If you see:

Could not find android.jar for API level 36


Install the API level:

sdkmanager "platforms;android-36"

Android SDK licenses not accepted

If the build says:

The Android SDK license agreements were not accepted


Accept them:

dotnet build -t:InstallAndroidDependencies -f net10.0-android -p:AcceptAndroidSDKLicenses=true

Notes

Make sure you always use .NET 10. Older versions might not work.

Always have JDK 17 installed for Android.

Restore MAUI workloads whenever you update the .NET SDK.

For iOS and MacCatalyst, make sure Xcode and the simulator are installed

dotnet run --framework net10.0-ios

dotnet clean             
dotnet build -f net10.0-ios
xcrun simctl shutdown all
xcrun simctl erase all


Renew the app every 7 days:


dotnet run \
  -f net10.0-ios \
  -c Debug \
  -p:RuntimeIdentifier=ios-arm64 \
  -p:DeviceName="iPhone - Panos"
